    {
      "id": "b68943b1f0cbcc064c059a543700a4b44b21f71a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-07 11:53:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nWith 1.11 I recall there were a bunch of new warnings added that had to be fixed or quieted in some manner.  Are there similar fixes that are needed with automake 1.12?\n\nNote I have a patch for quieting \":=\" assignments (http://review.whamcloud.com/3714) but IIRC it is broken for some reason that needs investigation.  Quieting any other warnings with automake 1.12 would be great.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a9fc3e20a938a0a80bfca48ea1f561939ceef2b8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-07 19:14:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nplease, have a look at the warnings I get with 1.12 (posted to LU-2290).\nactually it's quite similar with what I get on centos-6.4 and 1.11",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "77ca052530250f0b300db41a6af521845e4b610c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-10 21:37:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nWarnings are not the fault of automake-1.12, but rather autoconf-2.68.  That should be fixed in a separate patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
